ompassion with dr james doty and jon kabat zinn 12 14 2011 jon kabat zinn's life work has been largely dedicated to bringing mindfulness into the mainstream of medicine and society kabat zinn is the author or co author of many scientific papers on mindfulness and its clinical applications he has written two bestselling books full catastrophe living using the wisdom of your body and mind to face stress pain and illness delta 1991 and wherever you go there you are mindfulness meditation in everyday life hyperion 1994 kabat zinn has made significant contributions to modern health care with his research which focused on mind body interactions for healing and on various clinical applications of mindfulness meditation training for people with chronic pain and or stress related disorders the compassionate instinct a darwinian tale of survival of the kindest dacher keltner ph d is a professor of psychology at uc berkeley and the faculty director of the university's greater good science center an interdisciplinary center that disseminates the new science of happiness and compassion to educators parents mental health workers and others james doty speaking at tedxgoldengateed 2011 james doty speaking at tedxgoldengateed 2011 the science of self compassion dr kristin neff the science of self compassion read more jonathan haidt when compassion leads to sacrilege when compassion leads to sacrilege why conservatives and liberals have such different beliefs about helping those in need michael w kraus noblesse oblige empathy compassion and social class in america you may have encountered michael w kraus's work in the following recent articles are poorer people better at reading others emotions in the ny times or wealth poverty and compassion in the economist or heard him talking about class & emotion on npr now you can come hear him discuss his work in person compassion at stanford university 05 25 2011 watch this inspiring video of members of the stanford university community shari